## Actions (agent surface)

`src/actions.ts` exports an `actions` object â€” each entry becomes an agent-callable tool via `space_run_action`.

```ts
export const actions = {
  createTask: {
    description: 'Create a task',
    params: {
      title: { type: 'string', required: true },
      priority: { type: 'string', required: false },
    },
    run: async (p: any) => ({ task: await tasks.create(p) }),
  },
}
```

The agent (configured in `agent/config.md`) calls `space_list_actions` then `space_run_action`. Keep descriptions tight and specific â€” they're the only docstring the agent sees.

---

## Drag and drop (HTML5)

Tauri intercepts native drag-drop by default. The Construct host sets `dragDropEnabled: false` so HTML5 events fire normally â€” use `draggable="true"`, `@dragstart`, `@dragover.prevent`, `@drop`. No extra deps required; reach for `vuedraggable` only if reordering needs auto-scroll/animation.

---

## Conventions

- **Imports**: `@construct-space/*` packages always external. Local imports use relative paths (no `@/` alias unless you add one).
- **Composables**: `use*` prefix, keep in `src/composables/`.
- **Pages**: filename = route path. `index.vue` â†’ `/`, `settings.vue` â†’ `/settings`, `[id].vue` â†’ param.
- **Styling**: Tailwind utilities + CSS vars `--app-foreground`, `--app-background`, `--app-muted`, `--app-border`, `--app-accent`. Don't hard-code colors; the host themes via these variables.
- **Comments**: explain *why*, not *what*. Skip TODOs in committed code.
- **No emojis** in source unless the user requests them.

